org.hotteam67.firebaseviewer.tableview

Class MainTableAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.evrencoskun.tableview.adapter.AbstractTableAdapter<ColumnHeaderModel,RowHeaderModel,CellModel>
      • org.hotteam67.firebaseviewer.tableview.MainTableAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.evrencoskun.tableview.adapter.ITableAdapter

    public class MainTableAdapter
extends com.evrencoskun.tableview.adapter.AbstractTableAdapter<ColumnHeaderModel,RowHeaderModel,CellModel>
    The adapter responsible for populating views based on the data model. Basically just three adapters for a RecyclerView built into one, for rows/columns/cells. A note about ViewType: it can be used to create different holders with more sophisticated data, this program only uses one type for everything
